Detailed Description

template<template< size_t > class ValueType = SymbolicSemantics::ValueType>
class BinaryAnalysis::InstructionSemantics::SymbolicSemantics::State< ValueType >

Entire machine state.

The state holds the set of registers, their values, and the list of all memory locations.

void BinaryAnalysis::InstructionSemantics::SymbolicSemantics::State< ValueType >::discard_popped_memory (  )  [inline]

Removes from memory those values at addresses below the current stack pointer.

This is automatically called after each instruction if the policy's p_discard_popped_memory property is set.
